  "prompt": "How do I take admission in JNU?",
  "response": "Taking admission to Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU) involves several steps. Here is a general outline of the process:\n\n1. **Stay Updated**: Monitor JNU's official website or other trustworthy sources for announcements regarding admissions, application dates, eligibility criteria, and entrance examinations.\n\n2. **Eligibility Check**: Make sure you meet the eligibility criteria for the course you are interested in. Eligibility requirements often include minimum academic qualifications and other specific criteria depending on the program.\n\n3. **Fill the Application Form**: Once admissions are announced, you need to fill out the application form available on JNU's official website. This usually includes providing personal details, academic qualifications, and any other required information.\n\n4. **Application Fee**: Pay the application fee online as mentioned in the admission notification. The fee amount and payment methods will be specified in the guidelines.\n\n5. **Entrance Examination**: Most programs at JNU require candidates to appear for an entrance examination. Details about the syllabus, exam pattern, and other specifics will be provided on the official website.\n\n6. **Admit Card**: Download the admit card for the entrance examination from the university\u2019s website. The admit card will contain important information regarding your exam date, venue, and instructions.\n\n7. **Entrance Exam and Results**: Appear for the entrance exam on the scheduled date. Once results are announced, check if you have qualified.\n\n8. **Merit List and Admission Offer**: If you qualify for the entrance examination, you will be called for further processes such as counseling or interview, depending on the program. JNU will release a merit list based on the entrance exam scores.\n\n9. **Document Verification and Fee Payment**: If selected, you will need to attend the document verification process. Submit the necessary documents and pay the required admission fees.\n\n10. **Final Admission**: After successfully completing all the above steps, you will be formally admitted to the program.\n\nBe sure to regularly check the official JNU website and stay informed about any changes or updates in the admission process.",
